{"article_id":"DKhfCualII2WY0Dx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Lois G. Lerner , the woman at the center of the IRS tea party targeting scandal , retired from the agency Monday morning","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"after an internal investigation found","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"she was guilty of \" neglect of duties \"","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"and was going to call for her ouster ,","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"according to congressional staff .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Her departure marks the first government official","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"to pay a significant price in the scandal ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"though Republicans were quick to say","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"her decision doesn ' t put the matter to rest","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"and pointed out","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"that she still can be called before Congress","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"to testify .","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"The Internal Revenue Service confirmed Ms. Lerner ' s retirement in a statement","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"but said","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"it couldn ' t release any more information","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"because of privacy concerns .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Rep. Sander M. Levin of Michigan , the ranking Democrat on the House Ways and Means Committee , said","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"an accountability review board","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"set up","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"to investigate the people at the agency","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"involved with the scandal","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"completed their review","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"and were set to recommend Ms. Lerner ' s ouster .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"The review board , though , found no evidence of political bias ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"Ms. Lerner was head of the exempt organizations division of the IRS ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"which oversaw applications for tax-exempt status ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"including those from political groups .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Several congressional committees were examining her behavior and emails","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"that seemed to suggest","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that she was looking for reasons","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"to deny political groups approval for tax-exempt status .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Last week , acting IRS Commissioner Daniel Werfel said","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"he had asked a review board and the agency ' s inspector general to look at the emails .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Republicans said","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Ms. Lerner ' s resignation , while a first step ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"isn ' t the end of the scandal .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"\" We still don ' t know","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"why Lois Lerner , as a senior IRS official , had such a personal interest","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"in directing scrutiny","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"and why she denied improper conduct to Congress , \"","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"said Rep. Darrell E. Issa , California Republican and chairman of the House Oversight and Government Reform Committee .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"\" Her departure does not answer these questions","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"or diminish the committee ' s interest","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"in hearing her testimony . \"","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"But Mr. Levin ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"who called for Ms. Lerner to resign early on ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"there is still no evidence of political motivation in Ms. Lerner ' s actions or those of others at the IRS .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Republicans are stretching to create a political scandal .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"\" The basic overreaching premise of the Republicans","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"that the IRS had an ' enemies list '","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"and was being influenced from the outside","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"has been proven wrong again ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"as it has again and again , \"","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"Mr. Levin said .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"\" Just as the IRS has to move with all deliberate speed","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"to restore the public trust ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"so too must the Republicans","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"by not distorting the investigation","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"and by acknowledging the improvements . \"","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"Also Monday , one marquee tea party group announced","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"that it had reached a deal with the Obama administration","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"to approve its application for tax-exempt status ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"ending a three-year ordeal","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"in which it faced the same intrusive scrutiny","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that characterized the IRS efforts with regard to conservative organizations .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"True the Vote , the Texas-based voters ' rights group , said","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"the Justice Department and IRS agreed late Friday to approve the application for 501 ( c ) ( 3 ) status as a charitable organization .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"The group found out earlier this year","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"that it was part of a batch of hundreds of applications","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"that the IRS was delaying ,","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"and it sued","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"to force the agency to approve its application .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"The approval of the group ' s application does not end the matter ,","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"said Cleta Mitchell , lead attorney in the lawsuit .","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"She said","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"the IRS still needs to answer for the costs and damages","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"that resulted from the three-year delay ,","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"and for probing for information","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"the internal auditor for the IRS says","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"wasn ' t necessary","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"to make a determination .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Ms. Mitchell also said","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"Ms. Lerner ' s resignation doesn ' t resolve the IRS situation .","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"\" From everything","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"that we ' ve seen ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"the emails , the things","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"that drip , drip , drip out of the IRS ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"clearly she was involved in it ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"she knew about it ,","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"she has an agenda ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"as do others in the IRS , \"","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"Ms. Mitchell said .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"\" I ' d say good riddance ,","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"but the question is how much are we still going to be paying her , \"","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"she said .","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"Ms. Lerner has amassed more than three decades in government service ,","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"including 20 years at the Federal Election Commission","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"before moving to the IRS in 2001 .","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"She was appointed to be director of the exempt organizations division in 2006 .","depth":5},{"id":103,"text":"She was also a previous president of the Council on Governmental Ethics Laws .","depth":5},{"id":104,"text":"Ms. Lerner previously refused to testify to Congress ,","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"citing her Fifth Amendment right against self-incrimination .","depth":5},{"id":106,"text":"But","depth":5},{"id":107,"text":"when she appeared before Congress ,","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"she also delivered a brief statement","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"claiming innocence ,","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"which some members of the House oversight committee said","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"means she waived her right to silence .","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"Jay Sekulow , chief counsel at the American Center for Law and Justice ,","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"which is representing 41 conservative groups","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"battling the IRS ,","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"said","depth":5},{"id":116,"text":"her retirement is \" just another troubling move \" by the IRS","depth":5},{"id":117,"text":"and means she will be receiving taxpayer-funded retirement benefits .","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"\" Her retirement","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"- along with her continued compensation -","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"is deeply disturbing","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"and sends the wrong message about accountability , \"","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"Mr. Sekulow said .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":245,"left":221,"right":244,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":184,"right":220,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":184,"left":156,"right":183,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":138,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":134,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":127,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":0,"right":126,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":125,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":124,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":133,"left":128,"right":132,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":7,"right":131,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":131,"left":8,"right":130,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":130,"left":9,"rig